### Problem04

Look at the Java code below (You can chcek 'Towers of Hanoi' in the textbook, but the code below is a bit different from the one on the textbook).

```java
public class RevisedTowersOfHanoi
{
    public static void moves(int n, boolean left)
    {
        if (n==0) return;
        moves(n-1,!left);
        moves(n-1, !left);
        if(left) StdOut.print(n+"L ");
        else  StdOut.print(n+"R ");
    }
    public static void main(String[]args)
    {
       moves(Integer.parseInt(args[0]), true);
    }   
}
```

If we do 'java test 3', the output will be _____(0)\___ _____(1)\___ _____(2)\___ _____(3)\___ _____(4)\___ _____(5)\___ _____(6)\___ (Try not to use a program to run it).

